cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.GR 

This paper deals with the problem of restoring high-resolution face images from blurry low-resolution inputs. This problem is related to computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves image restoration and enhancement. The proposed method uses deep Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) which are a popular tool in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for image processing tasks. The paper also mentions the use of exemplar-based detail enhancement which is a technique commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG) for image restoration. Additionally, the paper involves the generation of facial structures which is related to multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR) as it involves creating and manipulating visual content.
